        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "seer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as he was with and under Abiathar the chief governor of the house and worship of God; who, by his office, was to instruct and direct the people in those matters, whereby he had many opportunities both of sifting out Absalom’s counsels, and of minding the people of their duty to David, as he saw opportunity: which sense suits well with David’s scope and design. Or, ",
